<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Bromus</i> <i>rubens</i>, <i>Schismus</i> <i>arabicus</i> and/or <i>Schismus</i> <i>barbatus</i> is dominant or co-dominant with other non-natives in the herbaceous layer. Emergent shrubs may be present at low cover. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 75 cm; cover is open to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Bromus rubens</i> > 80% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (cf. Keeler-Wolf et al. 1998b, Evens and San 2005, Klein and Evens 2005).</li>
		
		<li><i>Schismus barbatus</i> > 80% relative cover with <i>B. rubens</i> present or lacking in the herbaceous layer (cf. Keeler-Wolf et al. 1998b).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> All topography settings and soil textures. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Bromus rubens</i> as an UPL plant. </div>
</div>

        
